            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="0"/>
                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>t aliave qua causa et <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> arbitrabitur quem p<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> annorum XXXV praese<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>prehensumque est iu<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Pii <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Part</abbr><ex>hici</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imi</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Brit</abbr><ex>annici</ex></expan> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> ------ se] quo<supplied reason="lost">dcumque</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">--- adversus h(anc) l(egem)</supplied> rem<supplied reason="lost">ve communem<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">--- neque si aliter consil</supplied>ium [habiturum<certainty match="preceding-sibling::node()" locus="value"/> ------
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Stadtrecht. Parallelen im Stadtrecht von Salpensa. Zwei Fragmente, die offenbar zum selben Monument (Stadtrecht) gehören, möglicherweise allerdings auf einer anderen, wenngleich zugehörigen Tafel; vgl. auch E. Weber, in: G. Winkler (Hrsg.), Museum Lauriacum. Schausammlung &amp;quot;&amp;quot;Römerzeit&amp;quot;&amp;quot; im Museum Lauriacum-Enns 1 (Enns 2006) 90. Abmessungen des erst genannten Fragments (Ubl, Nr. II/B-4): s.o.; Abmessungen des zweiten Fragments: (Ubl, Nr. II/B-5): 3,2 x 2,4 x 0.4.</p>
            </div>
